Kaduna State government has imposed a 24-hour curfew in Atyap Chiefdom of Zangon Kataf Local Government and Chawai Chiefdom in Kauru local government with immediate effect. A statement issued by Commissioner of Internal Security and Home Affairs Samuel Aruwan on Thursday afternoon said that “security agencies are containing the tensions arising from a clash last week over a farmland in Zangon-Kataf.” According to the commissioner, community leaders had tried, without success, to ease the tension which seems to have escalated. YOU SHOULD NOT MISS THESE HEADLINES FROM NIGERIAN TRIBUNE Buy and read digital replicas of your TRIBUNE titles by subscribing through E-VENDING Buhari Expresses Shock Over Boko Haram’s Attack On Gubio
